author.location: Sunny Gosport on the South Coast

posts.content:
There's a Classic Car show in Gosport, down at Stokes bay. I have no info on it But it's run by the gosporteers ( I think they are a charity thing ).
I'm just off down with the dogs so will see if there is any info on it.
If you fancy a nice little summer Fete, then Stubbington summer fete/show usually has a classic car display. I was going to take my split this year, but not sure I'm going to be able to make it. We usually go every year, and as I say , this was gonna be the first in the split and I have never seen a split there before, Usually get about 20 or 30 Classics maybe more and motorbikes.....if the weather is good it's a cracking little summer fete.

Andy,
There is usually a couple of splits at the gosporteers show.
